&lt;div&gt;
    &lt;div class="section-tag"&gt;Race Strategy&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;h2 class="section-title"&gt;Project Overview & Approach&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="grid-2"&gt;
  &lt;div class="card"&gt;
    &lt;p class="section-lead" style="margin-top:0; margin-bottom:14px; max-width:none;"&gt;
      To tackle the F1TENTH Time Trial without changing hardware, we focus on a software-first racing stack.
      Our system uses LiDAR-based reactive navigation to identify traversable free space, select safe and efficient local targets,
      and generate smooth steering and speed commands through Pure Pursuit-based control.
    &lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;div class="feature-list"&gt;
      &lt;div class="feature-item"&gt;
        &lt;div class="feature-icon"&gt;01&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;
          &lt;strong&gt;Fast local perception&lt;/strong&gt;
          &lt;span&gt;Continuously process scan data to understand track structure and obstacle proximity in real time.&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class="feature-item"&gt;
        &lt;div class="feature-icon"&gt;02&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;
          &lt;strong&gt;Gap-aware target selection&lt;/strong&gt;
          &lt;span&gt;Choose feasible local goals that balance safety, forward progress, and stability during turns.&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class="feature-item"&gt;
        &lt;div class="feature-icon"&gt;03&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;
          &lt;strong&gt;Penalty reduction&lt;/strong&gt;
          &lt;span&gt;Minimize collisions and rescues by improving robustness in narrow or high-curvature track segments.&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;

  &lt;div class="card"&gt;
    &lt;div class="placeholder small"&gt;
      &lt;div&gt;
        &lt;strong style="font-size:1.1rem;"&gt;Add a hero racing image, car render, or track screenshot here&lt;/strong&gt;
        &lt;p class="muted"&gt;Best choice: one dramatic F1TENTH car image with RViz or track overlay.&lt;/p&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;div class="track-line"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;p class="caption"&gt;Use this visual area to immediately create an F1 racing identity when the page loads.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;



  &lt;div&gt;
    &lt;div class="section-tag"&gt;Preliminary Demo&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;h2 class="section-title"&gt;Simulator Validation&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p class="section-lead"&gt;
  We have successfully configured the F1TENTH ROS 2 simulation environment. The video below should demonstrate the initial vehicle setup,
  occupancy grid map, LiDAR scans in RViz2, and the first closed-loop validation of motion and sensing.
&lt;/p&gt;
