  &lt;div&gt;
    &lt;div class="section-tag"&gt;System Design&lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;h2 class="section-title"&gt;ROS 2 Closed-Loop Architecture&lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p class="section-lead"&gt;
  Our system is organized as a clean closed-loop pipeline: sensor topics provide local scene information, perception modules infer free space,
  goal-generation logic selects an actionable target, and the controller converts this target into Ackermann steering and speed commands.
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="card"&gt;
  &lt;div class="pipeline"&gt;
    &lt;div class="pipe-box"&gt;
      &lt;strong&gt;/scan + /odom&lt;/strong&gt;
      &lt;span&gt;LiDAR and vehicle state input&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="pipe-box"&gt;
      &lt;strong&gt;Preprocessing&lt;/strong&gt;
      &lt;span&gt;Filter noise and structure useful local observations&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="pipe-box"&gt;
      &lt;strong&gt;Gap Detection&lt;/strong&gt;
      &lt;span&gt;Identify safe free-space candidates&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="pipe-box"&gt;
      &lt;strong&gt;Target Generation&lt;/strong&gt;
      &lt;span&gt;Select local waypoint or target heading&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="pipe-box"&gt;
      &lt;strong&gt;Pure Pursuit&lt;/strong&gt;
      &lt;span&gt;Compute steering and speed commands&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;div class="pipe-box"&gt;
      &lt;strong&gt;/drive&lt;/strong&gt;
      &lt;span&gt;Ackermann output to simulator or car&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div style="height:18px"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;div class="placeholder small"&gt;
